ZH: 悲欢离合，人生何尝不是一场戏。
EN: Joy and sorrow, life is nothing but a play.

ZH: 悲欢离合是生活的必然经历。
EN: Joy and sorrow is an inevitable experience in life.

ZH: 走过悲欢离合，才能明白人生的真谛。
EN: Only after experiencing joy and sorrow can one understand the true meaning of life.

ZH: 他们之间经历了太多的悲欢离合。
EN: They have gone through too many joys and sorrows together.

ZH: 生活中总是充满了悲欢离合的故事。
EN: Life is always full of stories of joy and sorrow.

ZH: 悲欢离合让我更珍惜眼前的一切。
EN: Joy and sorrow make me cherish everything in front of me more.

ZH: 好的悲欢离合都是成长的机会。
EN: Good joys and sorrows are opportunities for growth.

ZH: 没有悲欢离合，人生又怎会如此多姿多彩。
EN: Without joy and sorrow, life would not be so colorful.

ZH: 他们的故事充满了悲欢离合的曲折。
EN: Their story is full of twists and turns of joy and sorrow.

ZH: 身处悲欢离合中，他依然坚强地面对生活。
EN: Even in the midst of joy and sorrow, he still bravely faces life.

ZH: 每个人都会经历悲欢离合的考验。
EN: Everyone will experience the test of joy and sorrow.

ZH: 不要害怕悲欢离合，它是生命的一部分。
EN: Do not fear joy and sorrow, for it is part of life.

ZH: 只有经历悲欢离合，才能更好地理解他人的痛苦。
EN: Only through experiencing joy and sorrow can one better understand the pain of others.

ZH: 悲欢离合让我们更懂得珍惜眼前人的陪伴。
EN: Joy and sorrow make us appreciate the company of the people around us.

ZH: 心存感恩，悲欢离合也会变得更加美好。
EN: With a grateful heart, joy and sorrow will become even more beautiful.

ZH: 面对悲欢离合，我们需要学会坚强。
EN: Facing joy and sorrow, we need to learn to be strong.

ZH: 悲欢离合让我们更懂得感恩生活中的每一个瞬间。
EN: Joy and sorrow make us appreciate every moment in life more.

ZH: 没有悲欢离合，人生如何能够完整。
EN: Without joy and sorrow, how can life be complete.

ZH: 家常便饭里也藏着悲欢离合的意味。
EN: Even in the ordinary daily life, there are tastes of joy and sorrow.

ZH: 能够坦然接受悲欢离合，才是真正的智慧。
EN: Being able to accept joy and sorrow calmly is true wisdom.
